<TITLE> Tigers win toss, opt to field </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 17 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh won the toss and decided to field against India in the Idea Cup first Test at the Zohur Ahmed Chowdhury Stadium here on Sunday. Dense fog delayed the start of the play. After a second inspection, match officials decided that play would commence at 11:00am (BST). The home side included pacer Shahadat Hossain and former IPL rebel Shahriar Nafees while Shafiul Islam will be making his debut in a three-man seam attack. India will be without captain MS Dhoni, who was ruled out after complaining of a back strain on Saturday, and off-spinner Harbhajan Singh due to a stiff neck. Amit Mishra takers his place. Virender Sehwag will lead the side while Dinesh Karthik will assume wicketkeeping responsibilities in Dhoni's absence, Indian team manager Arshad Ayub confirmed on Saturday. Teams Bangladesh: Tamim Iqbal, Imrul Kayes, Shahriar Nafees, Mohammad Ashraful, Shakib Al Hasan (capt), Raqibul Hasan, Mahmudullah, Mushfiqur Rahim (wk), Shafiul Islam, Shahadat Hossain, Rubel Hossain. India: V Sehwag (capt), G Gambhir, R Dravid, SR Tendulkar, VVS Laxman, Yuvraj Singh, D Karthik (wk), I Sharma, Z Khan, A Mishra, S Sreesant
